.Dd April 15, 2026
.Dt B76PIPE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm b76pipe
.Nd Base76 streaming pipeline encoder/decoder
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm b76pipe
.Op Fl r
.Op Fl i Ar infile
.Op Fl o Ar outfile
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl -file-stream
.Op Ar message
.Pp
.Nm b76pipe
.Fl h
.Pp
.Nm b76pipe
.Fl -help
.Pp
.Nm b76pipe
.Fl -version
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility implements the reversible Base76 7-bit binary pipeline used by the
hexdec2Base76 project. It can operate in forward mode (bytes to Base76) or
reverse mode (Base76 to bytes).

Input may be provided as a message argument or read from a file. Output may be
written to a file or to standard output.

The program operates in a streaming topology: input is read in chunks, Stage 1
output (if enabled) is emitted immediately to standard error, and the final
Stage 2 output is written only once at the end.

Although input is streamed, the Base76 pipeline requires maintaining a growing
big-integer representation of the entire message. Memory usage therefore grows
with input size.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl r
Run the pipeline in reverse mode (Base76 to bytes).
.It Fl i Ar infile
Read input from
.Ar infile .
Use
.Sq -
to read from standard input.
.It Fl o Ar outfile
Write final Stage 2 output to
.Ar outfile .
If omitted, output is written to standard output.
.It Fl v
Print Stage 1 intermediate tokens (per-byte Base76) to standard error.
Stage 1 output is never written to standard output.
.It Fl -file-stream
Accepted for compatibility. The program always operates in streaming mode.
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Display a help message and exit.
.It Fl -version
Display version information and exit.
.El
.Sh STREAMING
The program reads input incrementally and may emit Stage 1 output as bytes are
processed. However, the Base76 pipeline requires maintaining a big-integer
representation of the entire message, so memory usage increases with input
size.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
utility exits 0 on success and 1 on error.
